cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper involves the use of deep learning for brain age estimation based on structural MRI data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of large-scale datasets and feature-attribution techniques, which are common in machine learning research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the association of brain age with cognitive functions, indicating a potential overlap with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
